disease.description: A clinically and genetically heterogeneous disorder characterized by punctiform calcification of the bones. The key clinical features of CDPX2 are chondrodysplasia punctata, linear ichthyosis, cataracts and short stature. CDPX2 is a rare disorder of defective cholesterol biosynthesis, biochemically characterized by an increased amount of 8-dehydrocholesterol and cholest-8(9)-en-3-beta-ol in the plasma and tissues.

disease.description: An X-linked recessive disorder associated with a defect in sterol biosynthesis. Disease manifestations and severity are highly variable. Clinical features include intellectual disability, short stature, scoliosis, digital abnormalities, cataracts, and dermatologic abnormalities.
